==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castling
<hw>Cast"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is cast
or brought forth prematurely; an abortion.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Castling
<hw>Cas"tling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chess)</fld> <def>A
compound move of the king and castle. See <er>Castle</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cast-off</ent>⟦br⟧
